    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you, but it feels like you're dismissing the whole idea of national sovereignty or protecting our own workers' livelihoods as just a \"political\" tactic. if a certain industry is dying because of unfair foreign subsidies, isn't it a legitimate tool to level the playing field? why does the \"economic reality\" always seem to side against any kind of protectionism?",
