      "content": "While protecting domestic workers is a noble goal, relying on tariffs to fight foreign subsidies is a short-sighted strategy that ignores the complex global supply chains we depend on. The real problem isn't just unfair competition; it's that our own industries have failed to innovate and compete on efficiency, making them vulnerable to any trade barrier. True national strength comes from building a robust, competitive economy that can stand on its own merits, not from using tariffs to artificially prop up failing sectors at the expense of American families.",
